Adding back that extra term at the very end and factoring out $S$ again, we have $(1-x)S = x - x^{2012} $. This equality is then obviously true since when this series is taken to infinity, the value of $S$ diverges to $\infty$. <answer>$$S = \frac{x - x^{2012}}{1-x}$$
